cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.SD, cs.CY 

This paper focuses on analyzing and visualizing the semantic structure and content coverage of English Wikipedia, which involves techniques such as clustering and mapping. This falls under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with organizing and retrieving information from a large dataset. Additionally, the paper also touches upon topics related to Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it analyzes the co-occurrences of categories within individual articles. The use of measures and approaches to analyze and map the semantic structure of Wikipedia also falls under the sub-categories of Digital Libraries (cs.DL) and Software Development (cs.SD). Finally, the paper also discusses the roles played by highly productive authors, which can be related to the sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) as it deals with the security and privacy of online content.
